The cold front is expected in the Cape Metropole, in the mountain areas of the Cape Winelands and the Overberg districts. CAPE TOWN - Cape Town’s Disaster Risk Management said it on standby as a cold front was expected to make landfall in parts of the province on Monday. The cold front is expected in the Cape Metropole, in the mountain areas of the Cape Winelands and the Overberg districts. The unit’s Charlotte Powell said: “The city’s disaster management centre is ready to deal with any incidents that may occur as a result of the predicted weather.” The South African Weather Service also warned of rainfall leading to possible flooding. Strong winds were also expected from Monday afternoon along the southwestern coastline of the province. 